item.description:
In the 17th century, pagans in Lithuanians were often called by the euphemism &lsquo;Stara Litwa&rsquo; (which became &lsquo;Staralitva&rsquo; in Latin) in official records, a Slavonic term meaning &lsquo;Old Lithuanian&rsquo;
&ldquo;Why were the Lithuanian heathens most successful in holding out against the Christian steamroller?&rdquo; [MT16]
Thus, despite their many victories, broken by the Mongol strike and incessantly attacked by the crusades the heathen Lithuanian finally succumbed to Christianity in 1387 CE.
